s coming from harmonic analysis and physics; a discussion of wave packet transforms and their applications; and a new development of Howe's theory of the oscillator semigroup.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aHarmonic analysis. 0aPhase space (Statistical physics). 7aMATHEMATICS / Functional Analysis.2bisacsh  aAnalytic continuation.  aAnalytic function.  aAntisymmetric tensor.  aAsymptotic expansion.  aAutomorphism.  aBilinear form.  aBounded operator.  aCalculation.  aCanonical commutation relation.  aCanonical transformation.  aCauchy–Riemann equations.  aCayley transform.  aClass function (algebra).  aClassical mechanics.  aCommutative property.  aComplex analysis.  aConfiguration space.  aDifferential equation.  aDifferential geometry.  aDifferential operator.  aEigenvalues and eigenvectors.  aEquation.  aExplicit formula.  aFock space.  aFourier analysis.  aFourier integral operator.  aFourier transform.  aFunctional analysis.  aGaussian function.  aGaussian integral.  aGeometric quantization.  aHamiltonian mechanics.  aHamiltonian vector field.  aHarmonic analysis.  aHeisenberg group.  aHermite polynomials.  aHermitian symmetric space.  aHilbert space.  aHilbert transform.  aIntegral transform.  aInvariant subspace.  aIrreducible representation.  aLebesgue measure.  aLie algebra.  aLie superalgebra.  aLie theory.  aMathematical physics.  aNumber theory.  aObservable.  aOrdinary differential equation.  aOrthonormal basis.  aOscillator representation.  aOscillatory integral.  aPartial differential equation.  aPhase factor.  aPhase space.  aPoint at infinity.  aPoisson bracket.  aPolynomial.  aPower series.  aProbability.  aProjection (linear algebra).  aProjective Hilbert space.  aProje